---
apply_to: ["**/Cargo.toml"]
---

## Cargo workspace rules

### Mock workspace inheritance

- Every `arvo*` crate uses `version.workspace = true`,
  `edition.workspace = true`, `license.workspace = true`.
- Sibling arvo deps use `<name>.workspace = true` (declared once in
  `[workspace.dependencies]` as path deps).
- External deps (if ever needed) are declared in
  `[workspace.dependencies]`, not per-crate.
- Edition 2024 for all crates.

### Layer rules (dependency direction)

arvo is a four-layer stack. Cross-layer imports flow one way only.

| Layer | Crate | Allowed deps |
|---|---|---|
| L0 | `arvo` | (none within arvo family) |
| L1 | `arvo-bits` | `arvo` |
| L2 | `arvo-bitmask` | `arvo-bits` |
| L2 | `arvo-graph` | `arvo`, `arvo-bitmask` |
| L2 | `arvo-sparse` | `arvo`, `arvo-bitmask` |
| L2 | `arvo-comb` | `arvo`, `arvo-bitmask` |
| L3 | `arvo-spectral` | `arvo`, `arvo-sparse` |

Notes:

- `arvo-graph` / `arvo-sparse` / `arvo-comb` depend on `arvo-bitmask`
  (not `arvo-bits` directly). They reach bit contracts transitively.
- `arvo-spectral` uses `arvo-sparse` for the matrix layout. Spectral
  math doesn't need bitmask adjacency.
- The lint `forbidden-imports` in `mockspace.toml` encodes this
  table. Violations are rejected at build time.

### No external runtime deps (except notko foundation)

- No `std`, no `alloc`. `#![no_std]` crate attribute is mandatory.
- No platform crates: no `libc`, `windows-sys`, `nix`, `mio`,
  `tokio`, `async-std`, `rayon`, `crossbeam`, `parking_lot`.
- No allocator crates: no `bumpalo`, `typed-arena`, `smallvec`.
  Consumers own allocation; arvo never calls out.
- No numeric helper crates (`num`, `num-traits`, `fixed`): arvo
  declares its own numeric traits.

`notko` is the single permitted workspace-foundation dep. It is
the clause-dev primitive-vocabulary crate (`Just<T>` / `Maybe<T>` /
`Outcome<T, E>` / `Boundable` / `NonZeroable`), ships from
`github.com/orgrinrt/notko`, is `#![no_std]` with zero runtime
deps, and is consumed by every clause-dev repo (arvo, hilavitkutin,
clause). `notko-macros` and `notko-build` are pulled only when a
crate genuinely needs `#[optimize_for]` or build-time optimiser
distribution.

If any other optional crate is genuinely needed (e.g. cpu-feature
detection for a SIMD fallback), it must be behind a default-off
feature gate and listed explicitly in a design round before landing.

### No proc-macro crates

arvo does not ship a proc-macro crate. `proc_macro_crates = []` in
`mockspace.toml`. If a `_derive` crate becomes necessary, its
addition is a design-round topic, not a routine edit.

### build.rs pattern

Every arvo crate has a one-line `build.rs`:

```rust
fn main() { mockspace::bootstrap_from_buildscript(); }
```

and:

```toml
[build-dependencies]
mockspace = { workspace = true }
```

Mockspace's bootstrap writes `.cargo/config.toml` (`cargo mock`
alias) and installs hooks under `mock/target/hooks/` on first build.
Do not hand-author those files.
